---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import PageIntro from "../../components/PageIntro.astro";
import SectionBlock from "../../components/SectionBlock.astro";

const pageTitle = "Corporate Responsible AI Programs";
const pageDescription =
  "Ethotechnics-style critique of internal responsible AI principles, ethics boards, and review gates.";
const permalink = "/standards/corporate-responsible-ai";
const anchorLinks = [
  { href: "#overview", label: "What they are" },
  { href: "#critique", label: "Ethotechnics critique" },
  { href: "#failure-mode", label: "Failure mode" },
];
---

<BaseLayout title={`${pageTitle} â€” Standards critique`} description={pageDescription}>
  <PageIntro
    eyebrow="Corporate programs"
    title={pageTitle}
    description={pageDescription}
    permalink={permalink}
    anchorLinks={anchorLinks}
    panelCopy={{
      eyebrow: "Ethotechnics read",
      title: "Ethics theater under pressure",
      description:
        "Internal governance rarely grants stop rights to affected parties.",
    }}
  />

  <SectionBlock
    id="overview"
    eyebrow="Overview"
    title="What they are"
    description="Internal principles, review boards, and monitoring programs derived from broad ethics frameworks."
  >
    <p>
      Corporate responsible AI standards typically combine principles (fairness,
      transparency, safety) with committees, review gates, training, and monitoring.
    </p>
  </SectionBlock>

  <SectionBlock
    id="critique"
    eyebrow="Ethotechnics critique"
    title="Where the programs fall short"
    variant="alt"
  >
    <ul class="card__list">
      <li>
        <strong>Centralized review becomes a bottleneck:</strong> At scale, boards
        either slow the business or become routinized and symbolic.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Judgment-based governance is fragile:</strong> Under deadline pressure,
        discretionary controls degrade first while the system keeps running.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>The affected party lacks standing:</strong> Governance is inward-facing,
        not power the public can exercise.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </SectionBlock>

  <SectionBlock
    id="failure-mode"
    eyebrow="Failure mode"
    title="Ethics theater under pressure"
    description="Good principles and sincere people without enforceable stop rights downstream."
  >
    <p>
      The failure mode is a well-intended program that collapses into symbolic
      oversight when incentives conflict with restraint.
    </p>
  </SectionBlock>
</BaseLayout>
